Pre-Game Insights: Romania is seeking to win their third successive UEFA Nations League match.
Cyprus has appointed Sofronis Avgousti as the new head coach after relieving Temur Ketsbaia of his duties.
Cyprus has lost each of their last five competitive home matches by an aggregate score of 16-1.
Romania has not lost any of their last seven qualification matches across all competitions away from home.
Romania's head coach Mircea Lucescu returned to manage the national team 38 years after his first spell in charge.
